          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;By the age of twenty-five, [Louis T. Wigfall] had managed to squander his considerable inheritance, settle three affairs of honor on the dueling ground, fight in a ruthless military campaign against the Seminoles, consume a small lakeful of bourbon, win an enviable reputation in whorehouses throughout the South, and get hauled before a judge on charges of murder. Three years after that, he took the next logical step and went into Texas politics.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
